### Authentication API - Request Examples
### Use with REST Client extension (vscode-restclient)
### Or paste directly into Swagger UI

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = your-jwt-token-here

### ==================== HEALTH CHECK ====================

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/health

### Root endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### ==================== AUTHENTICATION ====================

### Register new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123",
  "name": "John Doe"
}

### Register user - minimal
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "Password456"
}

### Register user - validation error (weak password)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "weak@example.com",
  "password": "123"
}

### Register user - duplicate email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "AnotherPassword789"
}

### Login successful
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123"
}

### Login - invalid password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword"
}

### Login - user not found
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "SomePassword"
}

### Login - validation error (invalid email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "Password123"
}

### ==================== USER PROFILE ====================

### Get current user profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get profile - invalid token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token

### Get profile - no token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/profile

### Update user profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Updated Doe"
}

### Update profile - empty name
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": ""
}

### Update profile - missing name
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
}

### ==================== PASSWORD MANAGEMENT ====================

### Change password - successful
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "SecurePassword123",
  "newPassword": "NewSecurePassword789"
}

### Change password - wrong current password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "WrongPassword",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword123"
}

### Change password - weak new password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "SecurePassword123",
  "newPassword": "123"
}

### Change password - missing current password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newPassword": "NewPassword123"
}

### Change password - no token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/change-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "OldPassword",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword"
}

### ==================== NOTES ====================

@variable: Replace {{token}} with actual JWT token from login/register response
@note: Make sure to update {{baseUrl}} if running on different port
@note: Register a user first to get a token for authenticated endpoints
